BLENDER IE toolkit Package (V1.0.0)

===============================
 Introduction
===============================
This package contains information extraction toolkit which extracts ACE entities (PER, ORG, GPE), relations and events.


===============================
Major directory list
===============================
src/ ....................... source codes
bin/	....................... class files
doc/        ....................... includes this readme
lib/  ............. includes required third-part packages
acedata/ and data/	....................... includes models, resources that are used by the software
example/ ...................... example input, and output of the toolkit
props/	....................... property files defining major parameters in the toolkit
scripts/ ......................  sample scripts for running the IE toolkit
modules/ ......................  contains a name tagger developed by Qi Li
component.env...................... environment variables used the toolkit
enietoolkit.sh..................... main script of the toolkit
build.xml ....................... configure file needed to build the toolkit using ant

===============================
Usage
===============================
1. setting parameters in component.env located at the root directory of the toolkit
#set the home directory of the toolkit
ENIE_HOMEDIR= directory you untarred the toolkit



2. running main script
A main script named "enietoolkit.sh" is located at the root directory of the toolkit
The script executes as follows:
(1) Build the component from its source.
(2) Run a few sample source documents in example/sgm/, and output IE results in example/out/, a file list that needs to be tagged is in example/filelist
(3) Compare the output generated by the component against expected output (files in example/out/ace05_validate). Create a flag file called 'success' in the same directory as the script if the comparison is successful.

